gomodel:SYNGO_531  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" , "Rationale: Sodium (ion) channel, located in the pre-synapse. Contributes to excitability of the synapse.\n\n15/5/2017 Pim\n- Authors state: \"Nav1.2 immunoparticles were always localised to the extrasynaptic plasma membrane.\" Localization to AZ membrane is therefore not in question.. Experimental description: p.17: Tissue PreparationOF-1 mice from the day of birth (P0) to adulthood obtained from the Animal House Facility of the School of Medicine of the University of Castilla-La Mancha were used in this study for RT-PCR and Western blots, and adult OF-1 mice were used for histoblots and immunohistochemical analysis at the light and electron microscopic level. -- Highlighted 10 May 2017" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
